        <section id="requirements">
            <h2>Requirements & Professional Protocol</h2>
            
            <div class="protocol-box">
                <h4>üéØ Event Planning & Coordination</h4>
                <p><strong>Contact Person:</strong> All inquiries and coordination must go through Dr. Ayoola's designated contact representative who manages calendar, availability, and booking details.</p>
                <p><strong>Pre-Event Coordination:</strong> Event organizers must provide complete event schedule, speaker order, exact start/end times, and technical requirements at least 10 days before the event.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="protocol-box">
                <h4>üöó Transportation Protocol</h4>
                <p><strong>Pickup & Escort:</strong> Professional transportation with dedicated escort must be arranged for airport/train station pickup, hotel transfer, and venue transportation.</p>
                <p><strong>Air Travel:</strong> Business class or higher for all flights (domestic or international).</p>
                <p><strong>Standards:</strong> Vehicles must be clean, well-maintained, and appropriate to executive level. Driver must be professional and courteous.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="protocol-box">
                <h4>üè® Accommodation Standards</h4>
                <p><strong>Hotel Category:</strong> Three-star hotel or higher, where accommodation is necessary. Hotels must have good service standards and professional management.</p>
                <p><strong>Room Preparation:</strong> Well-appointed accommodation with complimentary WiFi, work space, and amenities befitting professional status.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="protocol-box">
                <h4>üé§ Event Protocol & Reception</h4>
                <p><strong>VIP Reception:</strong> Dr. Ayoola must be received at venue entrance or parking area by designated senior organizer or event director.</p>
                <p><strong>No Self-Registration:</strong> Under no circumstances should Dr. Ayoola be asked to self-register, find his own seat, or navigate the event independently.</p>
                <p><strong>Dedicated Usher:</strong> A professional usher must be assigned to assist Dr. Ayoola throughout the event, including seating, refreshments, and transitions between sessions.</p>
                <p><strong>Proper Introduction:</strong> Event MC or organizer must properly introduce Dr. Ayoola with full credentials and accomplishments before any remarks or appearance.</p>
                <p><strong>Visibility & Recognition:</strong> Dr. Ayoola must be appropriately recognized during the event. Failure to properly acknowledge his participation is unacceptable.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="protocol-box">
                <h4>üìã Event Requirements</h4>
                <p><strong>Technical Setup:</strong> Professional audio/visual equipment, microphone, presentation display, and technical support person must be on-site.</p>
                <p><strong>Advance Materials:</strong> Event organizers must provide event program, speaker list, and any other promotional materials at least 5 days before the event.</p>
                <p><strong>Professionalism:</strong> Poorly organized events that lack proper planning, structure, or professional conduct will result in non-participation or cancellation.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="protocol-box">
                <h4>‚è∞ Event Punctuality</h4>
